<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-11-21T00:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-11-21T00:30:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                    <head>209. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in India</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss><note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d209fn0">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                            691.93/11-2162. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>.</note></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>New Delhi</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-11-21T11:00:00+05:30">November 21,
                                1962, 11 a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                    <p>1973. Eyes Only Secretary. Verbatim Text. Department Telegram 2196.<note n="1" xml:id="d209fn1"><ref target="#d208">Document
                        208</ref>.</note></p>
                    <p><persName corresp="#p_DMJ1">M.J. Desai</persName> handed me this afternoon
                        copy Prime Minister’s response, dated today, to message contained reference
                        telegram.</p>
                    <p><hi rend="italic">Begin text:</hi></p>
                    <p>[This letter has not been declassified by the Indian Government.]</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="strong"><persName corresp="#p_GJK1">Galbraith</persName></hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>